# Refine Core Rules (this repo)

## Project wiring (source of truth)
- Refine app shell + `resources` registration lives in `src/app/layout.tsx`.
- Data provider is Supabase in `src/providers/data-provider/index.ts`.
- Auth provider is Supabase in `src/providers/auth-provider/*`.

## Package imports
- Data hooks and types: `@refinedev/core`
- Ant Design UI + table/form helpers: `@refinedev/antd`
- Routing integration: `@refinedev/nextjs-router`
- Supabase data provider: `@refinedev/supabase`
- Do **not** import `react-query` / `@tanstack/react-query` directly for CRUD pages; use Refine hooks.

## Hook selection (preferred)
| Scenario | Use |
|---|---|
| List page with pagination/sort/filter | `useTable` from `@refinedev/antd` |
| Read list without table UI | `useList<TData, HttpError>` from `@refinedev/core` |
| Show page | `useShow<TData, HttpError>` from `@refinedev/core` |
| Create / Edit form pages | `useForm` from `@refinedev/antd` — Refine v5 **infers `action` from the route automatically**, do not pass `action: "edit"` manually unless overriding |
| Dropdown select for a related resource | `useSelect` from `@refinedev/antd` |
| Create mutation | `useCreate<TData, HttpError>` from `@refinedev/core` |
| Update mutation | `useUpdate<TData, HttpError>` from `@refinedev/core` |
| Delete mutation | `useDelete<TData, HttpError>` from `@refinedev/core` |
| Resolve related records | `useMany` / `useOne` from `@refinedev/core` |

## Resource & typing rules (required)
- Every resource has a TypeScript model type (e.g. `type BlogPost = { id: number; ... }`).
- All Refine hooks must be typed (avoid implicit `any` in records/errors).
- Resource names must match the underlying Supabase tables (e.g. `\"blog_posts\"`, `\"categories\"`).
- Adding a new resource requires:
  - A route folder under `src/app/<resource>/...`
  - Registration in `resources={[...]}` in `src/app/layout.tsx`

## Data access boundaries
- Page/components should use Refine hooks (and therefore the configured `dataProvider`).
- It is OK to call Supabase client **directly** only inside:
  - `src/providers/data-provider/**`
  - `src/providers/auth-provider/**`
  - `src/utils/supabase/**`

## Anti-patterns (avoid)
- Do not fetch CRUD data with `useEffect` + `fetch` + `useState` in pages.
- Do not hardcode backend URLs in pages (Supabase is already configured).
- Do not modify `node_modules` to change UI—override via app code instead.
